&lt;p&gt;A24 is seeking an International Film Sales Executive to join our growing sales team. As a key member of the sales team, you will drive first-run film sales across a diverse slate, leveraging deep industry knowledge and established relationships with international distributors to maximize the value of A24&#39;s titles across global territories. This role requires frequent international travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to candidates based in NYC, Los Angeles, or London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initial Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with international buyers and distributors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute comprehensive sales strategies and valuations across film titles and territories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead deal negotiations for film rights and work closely with Legal, Finance, and Servicing to finalize contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing market research to identify trends, emerging opportunities, and shifts in audience behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and deliver compelling sales presentations and pitches tailored to individual markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep, current understanding of the global film and TV marketplace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure cross-functional alignment with internal teams on contractual obligations and A24 best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent A24 at major international film markets and travel to key territories throughout the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience selling first-run films&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in film valuation and international distribution negotiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong, established relationships with international buyers and distributors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine passion for film and building long-term partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial mindset with a solutions-oriented approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Humble, diligent, resourceful, and a team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seeks out new opportunities for growth&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness and ability to travel internationally at least five times per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for diverse perspectives. A24 is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourages applications from all kinds of candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our target salary range for this role is between $110,000 to $140,000. We do not use formal job titles internally and similarly named positions may have different compensation levels. Actual starting salary within the range will depend on various considerations, including: work experience, skills, specializations, and training. This role is also eligible for an annual performance bonus, including both cash and equity components, competitive healthcare, as well as other employee benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A24 is an acclaimed global entertainment company known for producing and distributing films, television series, documentaries, music, publishing, and consumer products. Established in New York in 2012, A24 has cultivated a library of over 150 films and 50 TV series, earning critical and commercial acclaim with more than 21 Oscars, 20 Golden Globes, and 19 Emmys. Renowned for groundbreaking hits like &lt;em&gt;Moonlight, Everything Everywhere All at Once,&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Uncut Gems&lt;/em&gt;, and &lt;em&gt;Backrooms&lt;/em&gt; as well as television successes such as &lt;em&gt;Euphoria, Beef,&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Ramy&lt;/em&gt;, A24 has developed a passionate fanbase and expanded into ventures like Half Magic and the Cherry Lane Theater.&lt;/p&gt;

