&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Financial Analyst to join our Finance team to support A24&#39;s growing TV business. This role sits at the intersection of deal analysis, corporate finance and operational execution — you will be the analytical engine behind our TV slate, building the models that greenlight shows, identifying areas of risk and opportunity, analyzing development spend and the reporting on KPIs. You will be a true business partner, working directly alongside TV leadership, helping to scale our TV business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a demanding role as deal negotiations move on their own timeline — term sheets, talent deals, and financial model revisions do not always arrive during business hours, and this role requires the responsiveness to match. In return, you will gain direct insight into how a world-class TV business operates, from how deals are structured to how slates are built.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deal Analysis&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain greenlight financial models for scripted and unscripted TV projects across A24&#39;s Los Angeles, New York, and London operations — incorporating episodic budgets, license fees, and multi-territory tax incentives to produce project-level P&amp;amp;Ls and ultimates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep command of residuals and complex talent participations — including backend structures, defined proceeds formulas, and guild obligations — ensuring these are accurately reflected in our models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model and analyze the interest cost implications of different production cash flow, tax credit and license fee timing scenarios to inform deal negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Business Affairs to model, compare, and contrast competing deal structures — evaluating the financial trade-offs between terms, rights packages, and financing arrangements, and providing clear recommendations on what creates the most value for A24.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop fluency across A24&#39;s range of TV business models, including: worldwide cost-plus arrangements with global streamers; deficit-financed projects with multi-window foreign sales strategies; and co-production structures with international partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and reconcile episodic and seasonal production actuals against approved greenlight estimates, maintaining real-time visibility into budget overages, scope changes, and contingency usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FP&amp;amp;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the long-range financial plan for the TV slate, consolidating project-level forecasts into a comprehensive annual operating plan and quarterly reforecast, integrated with A24’s corporate financial model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain dynamic cash flow forecasts at both the project and slate level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct variance analysis — actuals vs. budget vs. prior forecast — surfacing root causes of material changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build systems and processes to track, analyze, and report on development spend across the active TV slate — creating scalable infrastructure that provides leadership with accurate, real-time visibility into commitments, spend and KPIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the annual budgeting cycle by building detailed project-level budget submissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce regular reports for senior leadership (including&amp;nbsp; KPIs, budget pacing and slate performance).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
